OL,3,CIsle of Wight Council referred to
OL,4,Cadjudicator over school closures
OL,6,FThe Isle of Wight Council has been
OL,7,Freferred to an independent adjudicator
OL,8,Fover the process it used to close two
OL,9,Fschools on the island.
OL,11,FLawyers from the Diocese of Portsmouth
OL,12,Fnotified the council on Friday about
OL,13,Fthe referral, after its Cabinet agreed
OL,14,Fto close Arreton St George C of E
OL,15,FSchool and Cowes Primary School at the
OL,16,Fend of the academic year.
OL,18,FIt means the Office of the Schools
OL,19,FAdjudicator will now make a decision
OL,20,Fon whether the schools should close.
