OL,3,CIsle of Wight Council referred to
OL,4,Cadjudicator over school closures
OL,6,F"We have always acknowledged that
OL,7,Fthere is a need for the Isle of Wight
OL,8,FCouncil to rationalise school
OL,9,Fprovision. Clearly this needs to
OL,10,Fhappen again, but we are concerned
OL,11,Fthat the premises and fundamentally
OL,12,Fflawed positions that are still held
OL,13,Fby your senior officers will re-
OL,14,Fsurface and again cause unnecessary
OL,15,Fdisruption, distress and uncertainty
OL,16,Ffor children, families and
OL,17,Fcommunities."
OL,19,FThe Isle of Wight Council has been
OL,20,Fcontacted for comment.
